# Research

External sources, notes, interviews, and synthesis for {{PROJECT_NAME}}.

## Layout
- `sources/` - papers, articles, vendor docs (PDFs or links + summaries)
- `notes/` - annotations, organized by source or topic
- `interviews/` - transcripts and summaries
- `themes/` - synthesis: patterns and findings across sources
- `drafts/` - early writing that may move to `content/` or `planning/`

## Rules
- Every source has a citation: author, title, year, URL or DOI, date accessed.
- Notes link back to the source they came from.
- Direct quotes are clearly marked and attributed. No paraphrasing without attribution.
- Themes written in your own words, not stitched-together quotes.
- Capture a one-line summary on the day you add a source. Don't let unread sources pile up.
- Stale or contradicted sources are marked, not deleted.

